Mxolisi Mngadi Police say four people died when two cars collided and caught alight in Southport, south coast of KZN. (Supplied, Netcare911) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Durban – Four people have been killed after two vehicles collided and burst into flames on the N2 between Hibberdene and Port Shepstone, on the south coast of KwaZulu-Natal, police said on Monday. The accident, between a truck and car, occurred in the Southport area at about 21:30 on Sunday night, said Colonel Thembeka Mbhele. "Three occupants of the Light Duty Vehicle and one occupant in the sedan died," said Mbhele. Netcare 911's Shawn Herbst said reports from the scene indicated that the two vehicles had caught alight on impact. He said the deceased were discovered after the fire had been extinguished. A case of culpable homicide has been opened.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  